China raised today to 426 dead and more than 20,400 infected the swing of pneumonia outbreak caused by a new coronavirus (2019-NCOV) detected last December in Wuhan, capital of the Hubei Province (center), placed under quarantine.
The first person to die because of the new coronavirus outside China was a Chinese citizen in the Philippines.
In addition to the continental territory of China and the Chinese regions of Macao and Hong Kong, there are more cases of infection confirmed in more than 20 other countries.
The World Health Organization (WHO) declared on Thursday an international public health emergency situation on Thursday, which presupposes the adoption of prevention measures and global coordination.
